               <p>JAMES ASTON. I am a <rs id="t18280221-285-viclabel1509" type="occupation">wood-turner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-285-victim1599 t18280221-285-viclabel1509"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18280221-285-crimeloc1510">St. Luke'</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-285-crimeloc1510" type="placeName" value="St. Luke'"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-285-crimeloc1510" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-285-off1507 t18280221-285-crimeloc1510"></join>s. On the morning of the 12th of February I missed my lathe; I found my back window broken; I had seen the lathe safe the day before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-285-person1600">
                  HUMPHRY 
                  PERRY
               <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1600" type="surname" value="PERRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1600" type="given" value="HUMPHRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1600" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I work for Aston, and was using the lathe till nine o'clock at night; I went at seven in the morning, found the window broken in, and the lathe gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-285-person1601">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1601" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1601" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1601" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live in Turnmill-street. On the 12th of February the prisoner brought me this lathe; I received information, and gave him in charge - he seemed anxious to go away; I am certain of his person; he escaped from the officer; he gave the name of Clark, and said he brought it from his master.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-285-person1602">
                  THOMAS 
                  HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1602" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1602" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1602" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I apprehended the prisoner, at his mother's, on the 20th, he said he heard I had been looking after him.</p>

               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I told the officer I had it from the prosecutor's son; whom I met in Red Lion-street, and he asked me to go and pawn it, and say it was my master's; he stood on the other side of the way, and beckoned me, when I was detained - I went over to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-285-person1603">
                  THOMAS 
                  HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1603" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1603" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1603" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He gave this account on the 21st, the day he was committed; and the prosecutor's son said he had not seen the prisoner for six weeks; I knew the prisoner before; I went two or three times before I could find him; when I at first took him, he said he did not know the prosecutor's son.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-285-person1604">
                  JAMES 
                  ASTON
               <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1604" type="surname" value="ASTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1604" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-285-person1604" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My son had left me, and I told the officer to take him, as I had some suspicion of him.</p>
